defaultErdogan
default Government has also recognised the long-term security implications of what is happening inside 
defaultSyria
default. If you really observe clearly, the Turkish Government are moving more and more towards believing in a political solution. They are no longer the spearhead of all-out war against Assad. They realise that their security is deeply and directly affected, and not just by the Kurdish element—remember that al-Qaeda elements are basically on the Turkish-Syrian border—and that affects the short and long-term security interests of Turkey.
default&#xa0;
default              
defaultQ25 Sandra Osborne:default Who is supplying arms and by which routes are they going? To what extent is each of 
defaultSyria
default’s neighbours facilitating or permitting supply of arms to 
defaultSyria
default, to either the opposition or the Government?
default              
defaultProfessor defaultGergesdefault:default 
defaultTurkey
default has always been the major outlet for arms and 
defaultmatériel
default for the opposition. After the militarisation of the Syrian uprising, 
defaultTurkey
default made a strategic decision to open its front, including free for all. When the western powers argue, “Why would you allow certain extremist elements to use you?” 
defaultTurkey
default says, “Look, we have open borders. We have made a decision to support the opposition. And how do we tell?” Any person can go to 
defaultTurkey
default—you do not need a visa now, so you have the 1,000 European or western individuals who mainly use 
defaultTurkey
default as the major outlet. I do not think that 
defaultTurkey
default has consciously either supported or allowed jihadist elements to enter 
defaultSyria
default, but 
defaultTurkey
default has had an open policy, even though in the last few months the Turkish intelligence services have become much more conscious and are targeting some of the extremist elements who are entering 
defaultTurkey
default.
default              
defaultThe new development in the Saudi policy—I am talking about open sources again; I do not have any intelligence—is that Jordan has become a major second front for certain Free Syrian Army assets trained in Jordan by American, British and other forces These are very specific groups. They are using 
defaultDaraa
default in particular as the major front to target the soft belly of the Assad regime. Saudi intelligence services in particular are in charge of the 
defaultDaraa
default front. 
defaultJordan
default is very important, but it is a more targeted and focused front, trying to achieve an operational breakthrough by attacking 
defaultDaraa
default, because from 
defaultDaraa
default you go to 
defaultDamascus
default, the 
defaultQalamoun
default and so on.
default              
defaultSo far the Assad regime is terrified about this particular front. In fact, once the major battles in 
defaultQalamoun
default, which is on the Lebanese-Syrian front, are over, which will most likely be in the next few weeks because the Syrian Government are investing considerable resources, you will see this as the new front. Assad will fight to show the Saudis that they cannot make a breakthrough in 
defaultDaraa
default, because that is a very important front. So we have 
defaultTurkey
default and 
defaultJordan
default and initially 
defaultLebanon
default. The Assad regime and Hezbollah have tightened the Lebanese-Syrian borders area, so few resources are flowing from 
defaultLebanon
default to 
defaultSyria
default. 
defaultJordan
default and 
defaultTurkey
default are the major fronts by which the opposition is gaining arms.
default              
defaultThe Syrian Government is being provided with major strategic assets by 
defaultRussia
default—we know that. There is also 
defaultIran
default, and the biggest story in this conflict is how 
defaultIraq
default has emerged as a critical player. The Tehran-Baghdad-Damascus road is really the lifeline of the Assad regime for a variety of reasons. Remember, the Assad Government requires tremendous resources in terms 
defaultof ammunition, weapons, petroleum, food and what have you. That is not just in terms of Iranians; you also have fighters. We do not know the number of fighters, but they are flowing from 
defaultIraq
default into 
defaultSyria
default as well to help some of the regime elements, particularly in 
defaultDamascus
