defaultShashank Joshi:default Taking the neighbouring countries in turn, 
defaultIsrael
default’s role is pretty minimal. It is engaging in sporadic strikes against Syrian targets where it sees a transfer of advanced weaponry, but otherwise, by and large, it supports the stalemate, which it sees as weakening multiple foes.
default              
defaultJordan
default was initially ambivalent, but once it had 
defaultUS
default forces stationed on its soil, it was eager to see much more done to minimise the growth of jihadist factions. It even suggested the use of American drone strikes from its territory.
default              
