defaultSyria
default. It still sees a victory by the opposition as tantamount to a victory by fundamentalist Sunni forces that would catalyse much greater violence and political upheaval in 
defaultIraq
default, but I think it is not an active player in the same way that 
defaultTurkey
default and 
defaultSaudi Arabia
default are.
default&#xa0;
default              
defaultQ39 Mark defaultHendrickdefault:default On the question of 
defaultjihadis
default, a lot of people are travelling to 
defaultSyria
default, and they are getting all sorts of experience and training. As we saw when we did our inquiry into North and 
