defaultShashank Joshi:default Yes, and I think this is where I would differ slightly from Professor 
defaultGerges
default, who said the numbers of European Muslim fighters and foreign fighters is fairly small. This is the largest European Muslim foreign fighting contingent in modern history, and the numbers are obviously much bigger if you include regional people travelling there. We talk a lot about the risk to the UK, and that is obviously there, but the bigger risk in my view is groups like ISIS and 
defaultJabhat
default al-
defaultNusra
default becoming entrenched in north and north-east Syria, and using that as a platform for attacks against regional targets—targets in southern Turkey or targets in places like Amman, where I think there is a much more permissive environment for these groups to operate. 
defaultIraq
