defaultBeirut
default.
default&#xa0;
default              defaultQ40 Mark defaultHendrickdefault:default Do you think there is anything that the West—meaning the United States or Britain and France—could have or should have done earlier that might have made the outcome in Syria less harmful and more manageable in terms of finding a solution that can lead to a Geneva II that satisfies most of the players in the area?
default              
defaultShashank Joshi:default It is possible that a more concerted effort to secure a diplomatic solution very early on, before the opposition had become so fragmented, before the extremists within the opposition ranks had become so powerful as they are now and before the moderate opposition had become so enfeebled,
default 
defaultmight have had more chances of success. I am not sure that that would have yielded much because at that time, 
defaultRussia
default’s position was completely unyielding as well. It is possible that we could have done much more to restrict the inflow of funds to extremists from non-official sources early in the conflict, particularly from 
defaultTurkey
default. That is something I think that could have been done much earlier on as well.
default&#xa0;
default              defaultQ41 Mike Gapes:default Can I take up this point about extremist connections? We heard earlier about the Iraqi 
defaultMaliki
